==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ringdove
<hw>Ring"dove`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A European wild pigeon (<spn>Columba palumbus</spn>) having a white
crescent on each side of the neck, whence the name. Called also
<altname>wood pigeon</altname>, and <altname>cushat</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ringed</ent>⟦br⟧
